AN unidentified man died while on an Airlink flight on Monday afternoon, 24 May. The passenger died while the plane was mid-air during the one-hour journey from Joburg to Bulawayo in Zimbabwe. Airlink spokeswoman Karin Murray confirmed the incident to Daily Sun earlier on Tuesday morning, 25 May. “Airlink sadly confirms that a customer passed away while onboard flight 4Z110 from Johannesburg to Bulawayo. We extend our heartfelt sympathies and condolences to the customer’s loved ones,” she said. It’s not clear what condition the passenger was in at the time of boarding the plane. Murray said they couldn’t disclose more information about the incident at the moment.